{
  "name": "city_route",
  "agents": ["city_route_researcher", "city_route_planner"],
  "tasks": [
    {
      "name": "research_cities_task",
      "description": "Research a multi-city route inside {destination} (destination_type={destination_type}) for a trip from {origin}. Trip window: {start_date} to {end_date} inclusive ({day_count} days → day_count-1 overnight nights). Traveler preferences: {preferences}.\n\nPace first: fewer cities with meaningful stays beat a packed hop-between-cities itinerary. Prefer 2–3 nights per city when the trip is short. For ~6–7 nights, research at most 2–3 overnight cities (e.g. Tokyo + Kyoto), not 4–5 one-night stops.\n\nUse web search to find: which cities are worth overnighting, typical nights per city for this length of trip, and realistic travel order (geography / train / flight).\n\nDo NOT produce day-by-day attraction itineraries. Focus on city selection, nights, and travel logistics between cities.",
      "expected_output": "A concise research brief listing a small set of candidate overnight cities (paced for the trip length) with suggested nights, order rationale, and a few highlight teasers per city (names only, not full day plans).",
      "agent": "city_route_researcher"
    },
    {
      "name": "propose_city_route_task",
      "description": "Using the research brief, propose a CityRoute the traveler can confirm before day planning.\n\nConstraints:\n- destination_type must be {destination_type}\n- Cover the trip window {start_date}..{end_date} ({day_count} days)\n- Pacing (hard): keep overnight city count low — at most 1 city for ≤3 nights, 2 for 4 nights, 3 for 5–8 nights, 4 for 9–13 nights, 5 for 14+ nights (nights = day_count - 1). Prefer longer stays over more cities.\n- Prefer ≥2 nights in a city whenever total nights allow; avoid one-night hops unless the traveler asked for a whirlwind trip\n- Each CityStop needs: city, country, nights (>=0), arrival_day_index, departure_day_index, reason, highlights (short teaser strings only)\n- departure_day_index >= arrival_day_index for every stop\n- Day indices are 1..{day_count}\n- City day windows must be contiguous with NO shared days: next city arrival_day_index must be previous departure_day_index + 1\n- Together, windows must cover every day from 1..{day_count} exactly once\n- sum(nights) must equal day_count - 1 (total_nights); or leave total_nights 0 to auto-fill\n- status must be \"proposed\"\n- Do not invent full day itineraries or Place lists",
      "expected_output": "A CityRoute object with destination_type, cities (ordered CityStop list), rationale, total_nights, and status=\"proposed\". Each CityStop includes city, country, nights, arrival_day_index, departure_day_index, reason, and highlights[].",
      "agent": "city_route_planner",
      "context": ["research_cities_task"],
      "output_pydantic": { "python": "city_models.CityRoute" }
    }
  ],
  "process": "sequential",
  "verbose": true,
  "memory": false,
  "output_log_file": "logs/crew.log",
  "stream": false,
  "tracing": true,
  "inputs": {
    "origin": "San Francisco",
    "destination": "Japan",
    "destination_type": "country",
    "start_date": "2026-09-01",
    "end_date": "2026-09-10",
    "day_count": "10",
    "preferences": "mix of big cities and culture; moderate pace"
  }
}
